----------------------------------- BEGIN-CRFCF -----------------------------------

NOTICE: UNAUTHORIZED MODIFICATION OF THIS DOCUMENT IS EXPRESSLY PROHIBITED.
EDITING PRIVILEGES ARE EXCLUSIVELY RESERVED FOR THE AUTHOR, DESIGNATED
CONTRIBUTORS, AND AUTHORIZED ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE AGENTS. DOCUMENT INTEGRITY
IS SECURED BY A CRYPTOGRAPHIC CHECKSUM; AUTOMATED VERIFICATION SCRIPTS ARE
EMPLOYED TO DETECT AND PREVENT UNAUTHORIZED ALTERATIONS.

0.  METADATA:

    - RFC:      CONCISE-RFC-000000
    - TITLE:    CONCISE RFC FORMAT
    - ACRONYM:  CRFCF
    - AUTHOR:   Richeve Bebedor <richeve.bebedor+vs-scripts@gmail.com>
    - CATEGORY: SPECIFICATION
    - STATUS:   DRAFT
    - VERSION:  000000 (0.0.0)
    - CREATED:  2025-12-20
    - CHECKSUM: <SHA-256>

1.  Summary:

    This document defines the canonical structure, sections, and rules for all
    CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents in this repository. It serves as the authoritative
    template for contributors, AI agents, and tooling.

2.  Contents:

    0.  METADATA ........................................................... 005
    1.  Summary ............................................................ 014
    2.  Contents ........................................................... 020
    3.  Document Status .................................................... 025
    4.  Normative Language ................................................. 030
    5.  Naming Conventions ................................................. 035
    6.  Structure .......................................................... 040
    7.  Introduction ....................................................... 045
    8.  Terminology ........................................................ 050
    9.  Goals .............................................................. 055
    10. Architecture ....................................................... 060
    11. Specification ...................................................... 065
    12. Issue Handling ..................................................... 070
    13. Security ........................................................... 075
    14. Privacy ............................................................ 080
    15. Versioning ......................................................... 085
    16. References ......................................................... 090

3.  Document Status:

    - This document is a DRAFT repository-level RFC.
    - It is not an Internet Standards Track specification.
    - It is intended to enforce,
        - uniformity,
        - clarity,
        - conciseness,
        - and machine-parsable
      structure across all CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents.

4.  Normative Language:

    - The key words,
        - MUST,
        - MUST NOT,
        - SHOULD,
        - and SHOULD NOT
      in this document SHOULD follow RFC-2119 and RFC-8174.
    - This document MUST NOT use MAY.
    - The key word STRICTLY defines absolute non-negotiable intent.

6.  Naming Conventions:

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents titles MUST be named in ALL CAPS.
    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents titles SHOULD be one word.

7.  Structure:

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST be in text format.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST NOT exceed 999 lines of text.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST be 83 characters in column width.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST start with 35 (-) characters
      followed by space separated BEGIN-CRFCF then followed by another
      35 (-) characters.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST end with 35 (-) characters
      followed by space separated ENDED-CRFCF then followed by another
      35 (-) characters.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST have the NOTICE for unauthorized
      modifications with the following format:

        UNAUTHORIZED MODIFICATION OF THIS DOCUMENT IS EXPRESSLY PROHIBITED.
        EDITING PRIVILEGES ARE EXCLUSIVELY RESERVED FOR THE AUTHOR,
        DESIGNATED CONTRIBUTORS, AND AUTHORIZED ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE
        AGENTS. DOCUMENT INTEGRITY IS SECURED BY A CRYPTOGRAPHIC CHECKSUM;
        AUTOMATED VERIFICATION SCRIPTS ARE EMPLOYED TO DETECT AND PREVENT
        UNAUTHORIZED ALTERATIONS.

        - This NOTICE format MUST NOT be STRICTLY modified.

    - All repositories MUST contain the following METADATA documents:

        - AUTHOR
        - CHANGELOG

            - This MUST contain the changelog of this repository.
            - Each entry SHOULD respect the 83 characters column width.
            - Each entry SHOULD respect the conventional commits
              1.0.0 specification as describe in this document:

                https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/

            - Each changelog item must be in this format:

                <YYYY-MM-DD> <action>: <description-small-case>

                Example:

                    2025-12-20 chore: update documentation

        - CONTRIBUTING
        - CONTRIBUTORS
        - EMAIL
        - FORMAT

            - This file itself.

        - LICENSE

            - This MUST contain the license of this repository.
            - This MUST STRICTLY follows the FORMAT file.
            - This MUST only contain two sections, METADATA and License.

        - METADATA
        - ORIGIN
        - PRIVACY
        - README
        - REFERENCES
        - SECURITY
        - WEBSITE
        - VERSION

            - This MUST contain the version of this repository in SEMVER format.
            - SEMVER format MUST adhere to the format defined in,

                https://semver.org/

              with few caveats:

                - This MUST be in the RELEASE.MAJOR.MINOR format.
                - PATCH version MUST be interpreted as MINOR version.
                - CRITICAL changes MUST be interpreted as MAJOR version.
                - RELEASE version MUST start at zero.
                - A RELEASE version of zero MUST NOT be considered stable.
                - A RELEASE version of zero MUST NOT be used in production.
                - 99 MINOR versions MUST increments the MAJOR version.
                - 99 MAJOR versions MUST increments the RELEASE version.

            - Only the author MUST have the capability to update the VERSION file.
            - Version numbers MUST not reach 3 digits.


    - All single-line text formatted METADATA documents MUST follow a single line,
      no end of line and no final new line format.

    - All list text formatted METADATA documents MUST follow a multiple line with
      line feed end of line and no final new line format.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST follow this structure and order:

        X.  Metadata:

            This MUST contain the metadata of this document.

            The metadata of this document MUST be in the following format
            and order:

            - RFC:      CONCISE-RFC-000000
            - TITLE:    <UNIQUE-CONCISE-DOCUMENT-TITLE>
            - ACRONYM:  <UNIQUE-CONCISE-DOCUMENT-ACRONYM>
            - AUTHOR:   <FIRST-NAME> <LAST-NAME> <email>
            - CATEGORY: (SPECIFICATION | INFORMATIONAL | EXPERIMENTAL)
            - STATUS:   (DRAFT | REVIEW | STABLE | DEPRECATED | OBSOLETE)
            - VERSION:  XXXXXX <X.X.X>
            - CREATED:  <YYYY-MM-DD>
            - CHECKSUM: <SHA-256>

        X.  Summary:

            This MUST contain the abstract of this document.

        X.  License:

            - This MUST contain the license text of this document.
            - This MUST only be used on LICENSE documents.
            - LICENSE documents MUST only contain this and the METADATA section.

        X.  Permission:

            - This MUST define the permissions for using, modifying, copying,
              and distributing this document and/or this repository.
            - This MUST contain the NOTICE for permission in this format:

                NOTICE: PERMISSION TO USE, MODIFY, COPY, AND/OR DISTRIBUTE
                THIS DOCUMENT AND/OR REPOSITORY IS GRANTED UNDER THE TERMS OF
                THE LICENSE AGREEMENT SPECIFIED IN THE LICENSE FILE.
                PLEASE REFER TO THE LICENSE FILE FOR DETAILS.

            - This MUST be contained in all CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents.

        X.  Contents:

            This MUST contain the table of contents of this document.

        X.  Document Status

            This must contain the descriptive status of this document.

        X.  Normative Language

            This must contain the normative language of this document.

        X.  Naming Conventions

            This must contain the naming conventions of this document.

        X.  Structure

            This MUST contain the structure of the repository and/or this document.

        X.  Compliance

            This MUST contain the compliance of this document to this format,
            styles, principles and tools which includes any AI agent tools.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST follow this principles:

        - Single Responsibility Principle. CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents
          MUST address one and only one concern or feature.
        - Open-Closed Principle. CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST be open for
          extension but closed for modification. Once the status is STABLE, the
          CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST NOT be modified. New
          CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST be created for updates. If an
          CONCISE-RFC-000000 document has issues, then the entire
          CONCISE-RFC-000000 document must be marked for deprecation and a new
          CONCISE-RFC-000000 document must be published.
        - Liskov Principle.
        - Interface Segregation Principle.
        - Dependency Inversion Principle.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST follow this style:

        - Section headers MUST be clear, concise, and well-defined.
        - Section contents MUST only contain the following styles,
            - Descriptive paragraphs in normal conversational english language.
            - List that starts in (-) followed by single space and then
              the list item.
            - Formatted structures that is different from this format.
        - All formatted structures ordered components MUST be STRICTLY followed.

8.  Compliance:

    - All AI agents MUST STRICTLY read the FORMAT file.
    - All AI agents MUST STRICTLY add to their context list this FORMAT file.
    - All AI agents MUST STRICTLY follow this FORMAT file.
    - All AI agents MUST NOT STRICTLY edit this FORMAT file.
    - All AI agents MUST NOT STRICTLY modify the VERSION file.

----------------------------------- ENDED-CRFCF -----------------------------------
